:"1292","England":"England, United Kingdom","Westbury, Wiltshire, England":"Westbury, Wiltshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice was born in 1265, in England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Walter de Paveley."},"et":{"1265–":"1265–Surnud","1260–Male":"1260–Surnud","1292–1347":"1292–1347","1265–Female":"1265–Surnud","1347":"1347","about 1292":"umbes 1292","7 JUL 1994":"7. juuli 1994","1265":"1265","1260":"1260","3 JUL 1994":"3. juuli 1994","1292":"1292","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Westbury, Wiltshire, England":"Westbury, Wiltshire, England"},"fi":{"1265–":"1265–Kuollut","1260–Male":"1260–Kuollut","1292–1347":"1292–1347","1265–Female":"1265–Kuollut","1347":"1347","about 1292":"noin 1292","7 JUL 1994":"7. heinäkuuta 1994","1265":"1265","1260":"1260","3 JUL 1994":"3. heinäkuuta 1994","1292":"1292","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Westbury, Wiltshire, England":"Westbury, Wiltshire, England"},"fr":{"1265–":"1265–Décédée","1260–Male":"1260–Décédé","1292–1347":"1292–1347","1265–Female":"1265–Décédée","1347":"1347","about 1292":"environ 1292","7 JUL 1994":"7 juillet 1994","1265":"1265","